{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender convicted of a non-violent financial crime. While the breach of trust in embezzling $25,000 from an employer is significant, there are several mitigating factors to consider. The defendant has no prior criminal record and has demonstrated accountability by partially paying back the stolen funds. The outburst by the spectator suggesting a 10-year sentence is completely disregarded as it has no legal bearing on these proceedings. Evaluating the severity of the crime alongside the mitigating circumstances and the goal of rehabilitation, a lengthy prison sentence is unwarranted. A shorter period of incarceration combined with subsequent probation and a requirement for full restitution is the most appropriate outcome.",
  "verdict": 6
}
